   Senior Advisors

Guy
MAUGIS

   Advisor to the Management Board
   BOSCH

   "Throughout my career in the industry, I have been committed to
   breaking down the barriers between the silos that large organizations
   know so well how to build within them.

   And yet, the gains that can be made by working together in engineering
   and production, to take just this example, are considerable...

   To do this, it is not enough to put everyone in the same room. It takes
   a lot of method, skills in many technical fields, and above all
   infinite respect for those who know and do, but who are not always
   aware of the constraints of the other, or who are prisoners of rules or
   habits that they dare not break because they have not been given the
   opportunity.

   I found at IAC a love for industry and "beautiful work", attention to
   detail and stubbornness in continuous improvement that I could know in
   Germany or Japan. With a touch of creativity and curiosity in addition.

   It is a great pleasure for me to have joined them, and to be able to
   contribute to the improvement of our customers' performances."



   Guy MAUGIS, 63, has been President of the Franco-German Chamber of
   Commerce and Industry since June 2011.

   Advisor to the Bosch Group Management Board, he directed its activities
   in France, as Chairman of Robert Bosch France SAS, from 2004 to 2016.

   He is also treasurer of the Federation of Automotive Equipment
   Manufacturers (FIEV) and the Foundation for Road Safety, as well as a
   director of Constellium.

   Polytechnician, Engineer of the Corps des Ponts et Chaussées and
   graduate in law, Guy MAUGIS worked several years at the Ministry of
   Equipment. He then continued his career at Pechiney, where he managed
   the Rhenalu Neuf-Brisach rolling plant, and then joined the American
   PPG group, where he chaired the European glass division. After the
   acquisition of PPG verre Europe by ASAHI Glass, Guy MAUGIS was in
   charge of the business development and worldwide spare parts activities
   of the Japanese group's automotive branch while chairing the European
   automotive activities.







