Henri
BROCHET

   Former Deputy Managing Director
   THALES ALENIA SPACE

   "I love the industrial world in all its technical, technological and
   human aspects. I have always been passionate about team commitment to
   progress, introduce innovations and breakthroughs, but also make
   incremental improvements, step by step, with the ultimate goal of
   improving product and service performance, for the greater benefit of
   business competitiveness and customer satisfaction.

   I have known IAC for a long time, we have had several common
   experiences and my teams have always been very satisfied with the way
   they conducted the intervention and the results achieved.

   Their positioning on the reduction of direct, recurring and
   non-recurring design, development and production costs is major for
   improving the competitiveness of companies.

   They have very good engineers who are on the ground and know the
   aeronautics and defence professions well, with the interest of having
   worked with many companies in the field, but also those in the
   transport, automotive and mass distribution sectors, this is a
   guarantee of openness and synergies.

   They implement a pragmatic methodology, proven for more than 30 years
   in all industrial sectors, based on expertise in business cost drivers,
   and their proprietary benchmarking and costing tools place economics at
   the heart of projects and guide teams towards the best cost-performance
   trade-offs."




   Henri BROCHET has dedicated most of his career to the industrial world.

   He has held several management positions in groups such as Alcatel and
   Thales. He has been very involved in Europe’s largest space projects.
   It has been leading industrial entities with up to 3500 employees and
   including European subsidiaries.


   Henri BROCHET has been responsible for the integration of companies
   into Joint Ventures such as Thales Alenia Space in the space industry
   and has been involved in several M&A transactions. He has solid
   experience in everything related to the industrial field, production,
   transformation and improvement plans, Research and Development
   activities, management of large projects or human resources. It has
   also played an essential role in initiatives aimed at improving the
   competitiveness of the Midi-Pyrés region by participating in the
   structuring of the global landscape, in particular through the
   Pôtitivité, Public/Private Laboratories.


   He is always involved in the aeronautics and space industry as a
   director or member of management committees. Henri BROCHET was raised
   to the rank of Chevalier de la Légion d’Honneur in 2014.




