   Senior Advisors

Patrice
PÉLISSIER

   Former Chairman of the Executive Board of
   MEA AG

   « I have spent most of my career with Franco-German industrial groups,
   which have three things in common: the search to improve their
   competitiveness, an international ambition and the seek for synergies
   to overcome their cultural differences.


   A major movement has grown since the 2000s, major French and German
   groups are increasingly cooperating and are dragging other European
   countries along with them. This fundamental shift reflects a strong
   trend in the industrial world: to succeed, it is necessary to build
   competitive companies capable of competing at an international level.


   I found at IAC Partners this ambition: to build an agile structure,
   with a DNA focused on improving competitiveness, but above all, with an
   international focus.


   My objective will be to put my experience at the service of IAC
   Partners and to challenge their strategy, in short, to increase their
   skills thanks to my 30 years of experience in the European industrial
   world. »



   Patrice has held strategic positions in major groups and MidCap for
   more than 30 years.

   He began his career as a project manager with Michel Rocard and quickly
   evolved in an industrial context of Franco-German cooperation. His
   career reflects a strong attachment to this cooperation, which he
   highlights both during his interventions in prestigious schools (HEC,
   ESSEC, Science Po), as well as during his career in industry.

   His management positions have led him to study the key success factors
   for manufacturers: competitiveness, research and development, industry
   4.0, etc.

   By working in a bilingual environment, Patrice has developed a strong
   attachment to this dual culture. Co-founder of the Franco-German
   think-thank "Mittelstandslab", he shares his ideas and publishes
   articles on Franco-German economic relations, in the magazine
   "Confrontations Europe".

