     __________________________________________________________________


   Emmanuel has been driving his career as an industry leader for over 25
   years, mainly in the energy field. Emmanuel began his career at
   Schneider Electric (10 years) where he held various positions including
   General Manager of Units before joining Alstom Grid (5 years) to assume
   responsibility for the Transformers and Medium Voltage Equipment
   Division as Vice President. Emmanuel then successfully manages NKM
   Noell Special Cranes (3 years) as CEO and General Cable Europe (6
   years) as CEO / President. He joined the private equity fund GIMV (2
   years) as Partner for Energy and Industry before being appointed Senior
   Vice President of Global Business Transformation for Philips Lighting.
   Since November 2017, he has been CEO of  Leti.

   Throughout his career, Emmanuel has demonstrated in many multicultural
   contexts his ability to improve the operational and financial
   performance of the company;He was responsible for the Ebitda cash flow
   of the divisions he led, relying on the levers of innovation, the
   development of new systems and services and the vectors of
   transformation. Emmanuel has managed directly industrial entities from
   600 to 4500 employees and has recognized experience in Mergers &
   Acquisitions and LBOs.

   Emmanuel holds a doctorate in physics from the Ecole Centrale de Lyon
   and an engineering degree in computer science from the University of
   Technology of Compiègne (UTC). He also holds an MBA from the Grenoble
   Business School.




