   Senior Advisors

Philippe
GILLET

   Chief Science Officer
   SICPA

   "I have always been fascinated by new technologies and the sharing of
   knowledge. Throughout my academic career, I have been committed to
   building hubs of excellence and helping to train the scientists of
   tomorrow. As a supporter of a hands-on approach of teaching, I believe
   that to survive in global competition, our universities must
   systematically collaborate with companies. Beyond the simple financial
   aspect, this cooperation will lead the academic field to a more
   pragmatic approach in their disciplines.



   I joined IAC Partners to promote this vision of research and strengthen
   collaboration between these two worlds that intersect without knowing
   each other and are more dependent than they think. For industrials,
   competitiveness now depends on innovation. Price is no longer the top
   priority; consumers want to be offered new products and services all
   the time. The challenge is therefore to create synergies between the
   private sector and research, the latter with its long-term vision
   making it possible to guide strategic decisions."



   Philippe GILLET has dedicated most of his career to the academic world.

   Professor at the Ecole Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne since 2010,
   his research covers sciences such as geology, biology and astronomy.
   Author of more than 150 scientific publications, he continues his
   research and teaching activities at EPFL.

   Since 2016, he has held the position of Chief Science Officer at SICPA,
   a company recognized worldwide for its expertise in securing payment
   methods. This experience led him to develop an expertise on blockchain
   and crithomancies.

   This diversified career also leads him to promote cooperation projects
   between academia and business.



