Privay policy

   Use of the website
   Cookies Policy
   Data protection notice - prospects, partners and customers
   Data protection notice - Recruitment process
     __________________________________________________________________

Use of the website

   The personal data that may be collected on the site are as follows :

   Information from third parties : Some of your data (in particular your
   surname, first name and telephone, electronic and/or postal
   coordinates) may have been transmitted to us, by our partners. In this
   case, the processing of your data will be governed by these provisions.

   Contact : When filling in the contact form, your name, first name and
   e-mail address are collected.

   Cookies : Cookies are used in connection with the use of the Site, to
   collect certain information (in particular, your IP address,
   information about the computer used for navigation, connection mode,
   type and version of web browser, operating system and other technical
   identifiers or the URL address of the connections, including the date
   and time, and the content accessed). You can disable Cookies from your
   browser settings.

   Newsletter : When filling in the Newsletter subscription request, your
   e-mail address is collected.

   The main uses of your personal data are as follows:
     * Access and use of the site ;
     * Verification and authentication of your data ;
     * Optimization of site layout and operation ;
     * Managing the relationship with you ;
     * Sending commercial information and advertising messages, based on
       your browsing history, preferences and interests.
     * Sending news in connection with the company IAC Partners

   When certain information is required to access specific features of the
   Site, this mandatory character is indicated at the time of data entry.
   In case of refusal on your part to provide mandatory information, you
   may not be able to access certain services, features or areas of the
   Site.

   Your personal data will be kept as follows :
     * Data collected through the use of Cookies: Your personal
       information is stored for 13 months.
     * Data collected on the website via the contact form or newsletter
       registration: your personal information is kept for 3 years without
       any activity on your part

   These periods shall apply unless :
     * You exercise, under the conditions set out below, one of the rights
       granted to you by law ;
     * A longer retention period is permitted or required by law or
       regulation.

   During this period, the Site sets up the organizational, software,
   legal, technical means to ensure the confidentiality and security of
   your personal data, in such a way as to prevent damage, deletion or
   access by unauthorised third parties.

   Access to your personal data is strictly limited to IAC Partners
   employees, authorised by virtue of their functions and bound by an
   obligation of confidentiality. However, the data collected may be
   communicated to subcontractors under contract. the execution of tasks
   necessary for the proper functioning of the Site and its services as
   well as the proper management of the relationship with you, without you
   needing to give your permission. It is specified that, within the
   framework of the execution of their services, the subcontractors have
   only a limited access to your data and have a contractual obligation to
   use them in conformity with the provisions of the applicable
   legislation on the protection of personal data. Except in the cases
   stated above, we undertake not to sell or rent, cede or give access to
   your data to third parties without your prior consent, unless obliged
   to do so for a legitimate reason (legal obligation, fight against fraud
   or abuse, exercise of the rights of defence, etc.).

   Some of the recipients of the personal data collected are located
   outside the European Union. The following guarantees have been taken to
   ensure an adequate level of protection of personal data :
     * The recipient(s) adhere to the principles of "Privacy Shield" ;
     * The transfer is supervised, in accordance with the requirements of
       European Regulation n°2016/679/EU of 27 April 2016, by standard
       protection clauses adopted by the European Commission ;

   In accordance with applicable legal and regulatory provisions, in
   particular Law No. 78-17 of January 6, 1978 relating to data
   processing, files and freedoms and European Regulation No 2016/679/EU
   of 27 April 2016 (applicable from 25 May 2018), you have the following
   rights :
     * Exercise your right of access, to know the personal data concerning
       you ;
     * Ask for your data to be updated, if they are inaccurate ;
     * Request portability or deletion of your data ;
     * Request the limitation of the processing of your data ;
     * You object, for legitimate reasons, to the processing of your
       data ;
     * Oppose or withdraw your consent to the use, by our services, your
       details for sending our promotions and solicitations via e-mail,
       telephone calls and postal mail. This right remains valid that the
       information concerning you have been transmitted to us directly by
       you or by third party partners to whom you have communicated them
       (in this case, you will have to click on the unsubscribe links
       provided in our emails or contact us under the conditions below).

   These rights can be exercised by e-mail at the following address:
   contact@iacpartners.com For security reasons and to avoid any
   fraudulent request, this request must be accompanied by proof of
   identity. The receipt will be destroyed once the application has been
   processed.

   For any additional information or complaint, you can contact the
   National Commission of Information Technology and Liberties (more
   information on www.cnil.fr).

   If you have any questions regarding the use of your personal data
   covered by this notice, you can contact our Data Protection Officer by
   e-mail at the following address: dpo@iacpartners.com, who will process
   your application.
     __________________________________________________________________

Cookies Policy

   When you visit the Site, Cookies are placed on your computer, mobile or
   tablet.&lt;br&gt; A cookie is information placed on your navigation
   device by the server of the Site visited. Certain parts of the Site may
   not be functional without the acceptance of cookies by the user.

   Information collected in this way will only be used to track volume,
   the type and configuration of traffic using this site, to develop its
   design and layout and for other administrative and planning purposes
   and more generally to improve the service we offer you.

   This information will not, without your agreement, be kept for more
   than 13 months.

   You can disable Cookies from your browser settings. More information on
   https://www.cnil.fr/fr/site-web-cookies-et-autres-traceurs and
   https://www.cnil.fr/fr/cookies-les-outils-pour-les-maitriser.
     __________________________________________________________________

Data protection notice - prospects, partners and customers

   IAC Partners is committed to protecting your privacy.

   IAC Partners, a public limited company, is responsible for the
   processing of your personal data. The purpose of this document is to
   inform you how we use and protect your personal data, as well as the
   reasons for which we process this data, in accordance with the
   provisions of Regulation (EU) 2016/679 applicable from 25 May 2018.

   It applies uniformly to all services offered by IAC Partners, it being
   specified that additional information can be communicated to you if
   necessary when you subscribe to a particular service.
    1. What personal data do we process?
       We collect and use only the personal data we need within the
       framework of our activity to offer you personalized and quality
       services.
       We may collect various categories of personal data from you,
       including :
          + Identification and contact information (surname, first name,
            postal and e-mail address, telephone number) ;
          + Business information (position, company code to which you
            belong) ;
          + Banking, financial and transaction data (transaction data) ;
          + Interaction data with us: on our premises (contact reports),
            on our websites, on our applications, on our pages, on social
            networks, (e.g. during telephone or video interviews and
            conversations, in e-mails) ;
          + Video surveillance data during visits to our premises
       Unless required to do so by law, we never process information about
       your racial or ethnic origin, your political opinions, your
       religion, your philosophical beliefs or union membership, genetic
       data processing, your sex life or sexual orientation.
       The data we use may be collected directly from you or obtained from
       the following sources, in order to verify or enrich our databases :
          + Our business customers or service providers ;
          + Third parties such as commercial intelligence agencies, in
            compliance with with data protection regulations ;
          + Websites / social networking pages containing information that
            you have made public and databases made public by third
            parties.
    2. Special cases of data collection, particularly indirect collection
       IAC Partners may collect information about you even though you're
       not a customer. The following (non-exhaustive) list are examples
       personal data collected by the company from non-customers, such
       as :
          + Prospects
          + Legal representatives, corporate officers and authorised
            persons of a corporate client of IAC Partners,
          + Instructing parties or beneficiaries during transactions made
            in relation to with a client of IAC Partners,
          + Employees of our service providers
    3. Why and on what basis do we use your personal data?
          + To carry out a contract with you or provide you with
            pre-contractual information
            We use your personal data to conclude and execute our
            contracts, including for:
               o Provide you with information about our services ;
               o Assist you with information requests ;
               o Contractualize with your company ;
          + To serve our legitimate interests To carry out a contract with
            you or provide you with pre-contractual information
            We use your personal data to set up and develop our services,
            optimize our risk management and defend our interests in
            court, including for the purposes of :
               o Proof of transactions or operations ;
               o IT management including infrastructure management (e.g.
                 exchange platforms) and business continuity ;
               o Drawing up commercial offers corresponding to your
                 company's situation.
            These commercial proposals can be realized thanks to :
               o Segmentation of prospects and customers
               o Analysis of your needs on the different channels (visits
                 to our premises, e-mail, visits to our website, etc.) ;
               o Adapting the service offer in light of the data we hold ;
          + To respect your choice when we seek your consent for a
            particular treatment
            In some cases, consent is required to process your data for
            example, if we are processing for purposes other than those
            described in this Privacy Policy. in section 3, we will inform
            you and, if necessary, seek your consent.
    4. To which categories of entities will your personal data be
       disclosed?
       In order to accomplish the above purposes, we disclose your
       personal data only to :
          + Employees of IAC Partners, empowered because of their
            functions and bound by an obligation of confidentiality.
          + Service providers and subcontractors performing services on
            our behalf,
    5. Data transfer outside the European Economic Area
       In case of international transfers outside the European Economic
       Area (EEA) :
          + If the European Commission has issued an adequacy decision,
            recognising that country as having an equivalent level of
            personal data protection to that provided for by EEA law, your
            personal data will be transferred on this basis ;
          + If the level of protection has not been recognised as
            equivalent by the European Commission, we rely either on a
            derogation applicable to the situation (for example : in the
            case of an international transfer, the transfer is necessary
            for the performance of the contract), either on the
            implementation of one of the appropriate safeguards to ensure
            the protection of your personal data, or (standard contractual
            clauses approved by the European Commission, binding corporate
            rules).
    6. How long do we keep your personal data?
       As far as prospects are concerned, your information is kept for 3
       years as from their collection or our last contact with you.
       As far as customers are concerned, your information is kept for the
       duration of the contractual relationship and for 3 years after the
       end of the contractual relationship or our last contact with you.
       These periods shall apply unless :
          + You exercise your right to delete data concerning you, under
            the conditions described below ;
          + A longer shelf life is permitted or required by virtue of a
            legal or regulatory provision.
    7. What are your rights and how can you exercise them?
       In accordance with the applicable regulations, you have various
       rights, namely :
          + Right of access: you can obtain information concerning the
            treatment of your personal data as well as a copy of these
            personal data.
          + Right of rectification: if you consider that your personal
            data are inaccurate or incomplete, you can demand that these
            personal data be modified accordingly.
          + Right to erasure: you can demand the erasure of your personal
            data to the extent permitted by regulation and provided that
            IAC Partners is not obliged to retain them to comply a legal,
            fiscal or regulatory obligation.
          + Right to limitation of treatment: you may request the
            limitation of the processing of your personal data.
          + Right of opposition: you may object to the processing of your
            personal data, for reasons related to your particular
            situation. You have the absolute right to object to the
            processing of your personal data for commercial prospecting
            purposes, including profiling related to such prospecting.
          + Right to the portability of your data, where this right is
            applicable, you have the right to have the personal data you
            have provided us returned to you or, where it is technically
            possible to transfer them to a third party ;
          + Right to define conservation guidelines, the deletion or
            communication of your personal data, applicable after your
            death.
          + Right to withdraw your consent: if you have given your consent
            to the processing of your personal data, you have the right to
            withdraw your consent at any time.
       You can exercise the rights listed above by e-mail at the following
       address: contact@iacpartners.com. For security reasons and to avoid
       fraudulent requests, this request must be accompanied by proof of
       identity. The receipt will be destroyed once the application has
       been processed.
       In accordance with the applicable regulations, you are entitled to
       make a claim with the competent supervisory authority such as the
       CNIL (Commission Nationale de l'Informatique et de Libertés) in
       France.
    8. How can you find out about the changes made? to this personal data
       information document?
       We will regularly update this information document.
       We invite you to read the latest version of this document on our
       website and we will inform you of any substantial changes through
       our website and/or our usual means of communication.
    9. How to contact us?
       If you have any questions regarding the use of your personal data
       in question by the present document, you can contact our Data
       Protection Officer by e-mail at the following address:
       dpo@iacpartners.com, which will process your request.
   10. Miscellaneous
       Information about our cookie policy is available on our website.
     __________________________________________________________________

Data protection notice - Recruitment process

   IAC Partners is committed to protecting your privacy.

   IAC Partners is responsible for the processing of your personal data.
   The purpose of this document is to inform you how we use and protect
   your personal data, as well as the reasons why we process this data, in
   accordance with the provisions of Regulation (EU) 2016/679 applicable
   from 25 May 2018.

   It is dedicated to the recruitment process of IAC Partners.
    1. What personal data do we process?
       We only collect and use personal data that we require as part of
       our recruitment activity.
       We may collect different categories personal data with you,
       including:
          + Identification and contact information (surname, first name,
            postal and e-mail address, telephone number);
          + Professional data relating to training and employment (titles,
            diplomas, (e.g. work experience, references, targeted
            position, compensation elements, etc.)
          + More generally, data communicated by the candidate via his CV
          + Interaction data with us: on our premises (contact reports),
            on our websites, on our applications, on our pages, on our
            social networks, during interviews and telephone or video
            conversations, in e-mails);
          + Video surveillance during visits to our premises
       Unless required to do so by law, we never process information about
       your racial or ethnic origin, your political opinions, your
       religion, your philosophical beliefs or union membership, genetic
       data processing, your sex life or sexual orientation.
       The data we use may be collected directly from you or obtained from
       the following sources, in order to verify or enrich our databases:
          + Our business customers or service providers ;
          + Websites / social networking pages containing information that
            you have made public and databases made public by third
            parties
    2. Why and on what basis do we use your personal data?
       We use your personal data on the basis of our legitimate interest,
       and with the aim of conducting our recruitment activity.
    3. To which categories of entities will your personal data be
       disclosed?
       In order to accomplish the above purposes, we disclose your
       personal data only to :
          + Employees of IAC Partners empowered because of of their duties
            and bound by an obligation of confidentiality.
          + Service providers and subcontractors providing services on our
            behalf
    4. Data transfer outside the European Economic Area
       In case of international transfers outside the European Economic
       Area (EEA) :
          + If the European Commission has issued an adequacy decision,
            recognising that country a level of protection of personal
            data equivalent to that provided by EEA law, your personal
            data will be transferred on this basis;
          + If the level of protection has not been recognised as
            equivalent by the European Commission, we rely either on a
            waiver applicable to the situation, or on the implementation
            of the one of the appropriate guarantees to ensure the
            protection of your personal data (standard contractual clauses
            approved by the European Commission, binding corporate rules).
    5. How long do we keep your personal data?
       The data are kept for a maximum of 2 years without any activity on
       your part for the position on which the exchange took place. This
       period may be extended to a maximum of 10 years for future
       recruitment needs.
       This period is applied unless:
          + You exercise your right to delete data concerning you, under
            the conditions described below;
          + A longer shelf life is permitted or required by virtue of a
            legal or regulatory provision.
    6. What are your rights and how can you exercise them?
       In accordance with the applicable regulations, you have various
       rights, namely :
          + Right of access: you can obtain information concerning the
            processing of your data as well as a copy of these personal
            data.
          + Right of rectification: if you consider that your personal
            data are inaccurate or incomplete, you can demand that these
            personal data be modified accordingly.
          + Right to erasure: you can demand the erasure of your personal
            data to the extent permitted by regulation and provided that
            IAC Partners is not required to retain them to comply with any
            legal, tax or regulatory obligation.
          + Right to limitation of treatment: you can request the
            limitation of treatment of your personal data.
          + Right of opposition: you may object to the processing of your
            personal data, for reasons related to your particular
            situation. You have the absolute right to object the
            processing of your personal data for commercial prospecting
            purposes, including profiling related to this prospecting.
          + Right to the portability of your data, where this right is
            applicable, you have the right to have the personal data you
            have provided us returned to you or, where it is technically
            possible to transfer them to a third party;
          + Right to define guidelines for retention, deletion or the
            communication of your personal data, applicable after your
            death.
       You can exercise the rights listed above by e-mail at the following
       address: contact@iacpartners.com.
       For security reasons and to avoid any fraudulent request, this
       request must be accompanied by proof of identity. The receipt will
       be destroyed once the application has been processed.
       In accordance with the applicable regulations, you are entitled to
       make a claim to the competent supervisory authority such as the
       CNIL (Commission Nationale de l'Informatique et de Libertés) in
       France.
    7. De quelle manière pouvez-vous prendre connaissance des
       modifications apportées à ce document d’information sur les données
       personnelles ?
       In a world in constant technological evolution, we will update
       regularly this backgrounder.
       We invite you to read the latest version of this document on our
       website and we will inform you of any substantial changes through
       our website and/or our usual means of communication.
    8. How to contact us?
       If you have any questions regarding the use of your personal data
       referred to in this document, you may contact our Data Protection
       Officer by e-mail at the following address: dpo@iacpartners.com,
       who will process your request.

